/* Era definitions */ subdivision of Archean and Proterozoic eons - changed wording
/* Table of geologic time */Some further info. Removed the mentioning of only one ocean when, in reality, many oceans (maybe all except Pacific) were created due to the breakup of Pangaea.

Undid revision 1070063039 by [[Special:Contributions/2601:280:C601:2DB0:99FB:3E14:B2F0:55CD|2601:280:C601:2DB0:99FB:3E14:B2F0:55CD]] rv, which part of "Popular culture and a growing number of scientists use the term "[[Anthropocene]]"  informally " did you not understand?

/* Table of geologic time */Uh, but they did not become those lineages. And thanks for not including those condylarths, miacoids and cimolestans as the extinct groups in the Grand Coupere extinction event since they did not go extinct fully at the event but survived some million years into the oligocene.

/* Table of geologic time */Staying the least controversial on the O2 levels (based on the points many graphs agree). Mentioning the bears and hippos only for their size is kinda silly, so added them in epochs when they first appeared. (Angiosperms are thought to have appeared in late Triassic according to recent molecular clocks, but lack of any fossil from that period, and even from Jurassic, prevents me to do it though I have sources.)
/* Table of geologic time */ still needs correction.
